@startuml
title "SIWA Migration or Add Permissions Flow"
actor "User" as u
participant "UserAgent" as ua
participant "Provider" as p
participant "Frequency\nAccess" as fa
database "Postgres" as db
database "Redis" as r
participant "Frequency" as bc
participant "SES" as ses
participant "Notification\nService" as ns

note across: Assumes you are coming from the Login Flow
autonumber
fa->p: Callback for identifier(s)
return Other Identifiers associated or Empty
alt Empty or just the same identifier
    group Add Permissions
        fa->bc: get permissions for userMsaId, providerId
        return Permissions for Provider
        fa->ua: Render Permissions Screen for all requested permissions for provider
        ua->fa: Accepts
        fa->r: Find Session by id
        return Session
        fa->fa: create and sign addPermissionsPayload chosen key
        fa->fa: Add addPermissionsPayload to Session
    end
else Delta Migration
    fa->fa: Determine disjoint Set<UserIdentifiers>
    fa->ua: Ask which of the disjoint Set to verify
    ua->fa: UserIdentifier
    group Identifier Verification
        fa->fa: Generate authenticationCode
        fa->r: Persist Session by authenticationCode and sessionId
        return
        alt isEmail
            fa->ses: Send Email (sessionId and authenticationCode)
            ses->u: Email sent
            u->fa: User Clicks Email
            fa->r: find Session by authenticationCode and sessionId
            return Session
        else isSms
            fa->ns: Send SMS
            fa->ua: Display SMS Form
            ns->u: Sms Message received
            u->ua: Enters authenticationCode
            ua->fa: Submits authenticationCode
            fa->r: find Session by authenticationCode and sessionId
            return Session
        end
        fa->r: Update Session by Id (This sucks, because we violate DRY)
    end
    note across: See: Add Permissions
end
fa->ua: Redirect to callback url with authorizationCode, sessionId
ua->p: Resolve redirect
p->fa: Resolve payload by authorizationCode and sessionId
fa->p: Signed Payload
@enduml